      • applyExtensions

        protected ExtensionByteBuffer applyExtensions(ByteBuffer buffer,
                                              int position,
                                              int length)
                                       throws IOException
        Process Extensions chain before a write operation.

        An extension can modify original content beyond ByteBuffer capacity,then original buffer is wrapped with ExtensionByteBuffer class. ExtensionByteBuffer stores extra buffer to manage overflow of original ByteBuffer .

        Parameters:
        buffer - the buffer to operate on
        position - the index in the buffer to start from
        length - the number of bytes to operate on
        Returns:
        a ExtensionByteBuffer instance as a wrapper of original buffer with extra buffers; null if no extra buffers needed
        Throws:
        IOException
